        'To maintain Aldbury\'s pristine, historic character, underground motors are almost exclusively specified for premium installations. By housing the automation hardware beneath the driveway surface, the entrance reads purely as an architectural feature rather than a mechanical barrier. Because Aldbury sits on a mix of chalk and clay, our installation experts ensure that oversized soakaway systems are integrated into the underground foundation boxes, preventing the waterlogging that can occur during heavy winter rains running off the Ashridge hills.',
