        'Infrared lenses get blocked by sticky tree sap and woodland moss, causing false obstacle detections. When the control board thinks a car is in the way, it refuses to close the massive security gates. Servicing teams actively scrub the sensors, realign the optical beams, and apply specialized rain-repellent coatings to the plastic housings. This proactive maintenance stops the forest environment from paralyzing the expensive automation system.',
