        'Galvanising tanks submerge the raw steel, ensuring permanent rust immunity. Powder coated finishes applied directly over bare steel will peel within a few short years near the river valley. By dipping the fabricated gate in molten zinc, a permanent rust-proof layer is bonded to every weld point and cut edge. The final decorative color is then baked over the zinc, creating a bulletproof finish.',
        'Fabrication software maps the precise contours of the local terrain. Whitwell driveways rarely conform to perfectly square dimensions, often requiring custom raked bottoms to accommodate steep slopes plunging toward the river. The incredible flexibility of steel allows local makers to draft precise CAD blueprints that solve these physical challenges seamlessly, resulting in a heavy-duty entrance that fits flawlessly.',
